Despite the fraternal war of recent years, the Iraqi society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterised by the contraindication - no one can be relied on and no agreements are made.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they have been formally established correctly, remain only fictitious structures behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the various ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially due to the intransparence of the conditions, which further complicate Pakistani and Iranian influences.
The establishment of a “actable state”, which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation, is also very unrealistic.
Timeline of Obama’s strategy alienated by his voluntarism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and is now on the brink of the explosion.
