The team of Czech and German scientists is testing new compounds to prevent the spread of HIV viruses in the body.
The main advantage of the improved substance is that it also acts on the viruses that are already resistant to drugs.
This fact outweighs the disadvantage that the compound does not have as much effect on common viral variants as one of the already existing drugs.
The disease AIDS can not yet be cured.
However, the composition of the drugs can prolong the life and prevent the multiplication of HIV viruses in the body.
